snippet: Britain’s royal household rebuked a French magazine for photographs of the former Kate Middleton topless, evoking the furor around press coverage of Diana.
abstract: British Royal family is suing French magazine Closer for invasion of privacy after publishing paparazzi photographs of the Duchess of Cambridge, the former Kate Middleton, sunbathing topless at a secluded villa in Provence.

byline.original: By ALAN COWELL and JOHN F. BURNS

lead_paragraph: Britain’s royal household rebuked a French magazine for photographs of the former Kate Middleton topless, evoking the furor around press coverage of Diana.

headline.seo: Photos of Topless Kate Middleton Prompt Lawsuit
headline.main: Royal Couple Sue Over Photos of Topless Duchess
headline.print_headline: Royals Sue Over Photos Of Duchess, Top Bared
